---
const items = [
  {
    q: 'What is PAI?',
    a: 'PAI is a bootable live-USB operating system that runs local AI models entirely on your own hardware. No cloud, no accounts, no internet required.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What hardware do I need?',
    a: 'Any x86-64 PC with at least 8 GB RAM and a USB 3.0 port. For running larger models (13B+), 16 GB RAM and a GPU are recommended but not required.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I install it?',
    a: 'Download the ISO and write it to a USB drive using dd, Rufus, or Balena Etcher. Then reboot your PC and select the USB from the boot menu. No installation to your hard drive is needed.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it really private?',
    a: 'Yes — not "policy-private," actually private. PAI never connects to the internet unless you open a browser yourself. All AI inference runs locally via Ollama. There is no telemetry, no license server, no accounts, and no company that can read your prompts, ever.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What AI models are included?',
    a: 'PAI ships with Llama 3, Mistral, and Phi via Ollama. You can add any GGUF-format model by copying it to the USB drive. The model library is fully under your control.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I use it without an internet connection?',
    a: "Yes — that's the whole point. PAI is designed to work completely airgapped. Every component that needs to work offline is bundled on the USB drive.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Does it modify my computer?',
    a: "No. PAI runs live from the USB drive and does not touch your hard drive or existing OS. You can remove the USB at any time to restore normal operation.",
  },
]
---

<section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <h2 id="faq-heading" class="section-heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>

  <dl class="faq">
    {
      items.map((item) => (
        <details class="faq__item">
          <summary class="faq__question">
            <dt>{item.q}</dt>
            <span class="faq__chevron" aria-hidden="true">▸</span>
          </summary>
          <dd class="faq__answer">{item.a}</dd>
        </details>
      ))
    }
  </dl>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-section {
    padding: var(--s-7) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .faq {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-2);
  }

  .faq__item {
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-window);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color var(--motion-duration) var(--motion-easing);
  }

  .faq__item:hover {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pai-blue) 40%, var(--border));
  }

  .faq__item[open] {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pai-blue) 60%, var(--border));
  }

  .faq__question {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: var(--s-4) var(--s-5);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    gap: var(--s-4);
    user-select: none;
    min-height: 44px;
  }

  /* Remove default marker in WebKit */
  .faq__question::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq__question dt {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .faq__chevron {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    transition: transform var(--motion-duration) var(--motion-easing);
  }

  .faq__item[open] .faq__chevron {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  .faq__answer {
    padding: 0 var(--s-5) var(--s-4);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: var(--s-3);
  }
</style>
